Let me examine beta4's path handling in detail across all components.
I re-read all of beta4 carefully. There are path and naming inconsistencies that will cause runtime errors. Here's exactly what's wrong and how to fix each file.
1.  frontend/app.py — Config path is hardcoded to root, ignoring config/config.yaml
Problem: Line 245 hardcodes ROOT_DIR / "config.yaml", but the repo ships config/config.yaml. When you run beta4, the frontend crashes because it can't find config.yaml at the root. Also, start(app_config) ignores the config already loaded by main.py.
Fix:
In frontend/app.py, replace lines 244-246:
config_path = ROOT_DIR / "config.yaml"
loader      = ConfigLoader(str(config_path))
app_settings = loader.get_app_settings()

With:
cfg_file = ROOT_DIR / "config" / "config.yaml"
if not cfg_file.exists():
    cfg_file = ROOT_DIR / "config.yaml"
loader       = ConfigLoader(str(cfg_file))
app_settings = loader.get_app_settings()

Even better — reuse the already-loaded config from main.py by storing it globally, but the above is the minimal safe fix.
2.  frontend/core/version_sync.py — Stale remote path from beta2
Problem: Lines 21-22 still point to /opt/clusterpulse (the old beta2 name). Beta4's bootstrapper and backend use /opt/cloud_health.
Fix:
Replace lines 21-22:
REMOTE_ROOT        = "/opt/clusterpulse"
REMOTE_VERSION     = f"{REMOTE_ROOT}/version.txt"
With:
REMOTE_ROOT        = "/opt/cloud_health"
REMOTE_VERSION     = f"{REMOTE_ROOT}/version.txt"
(Note: This file appears to be dead code right now — nothing imports it — but if you ever wire it up, this path mismatch will break version syncing.)
3.  frontend/core/config.py — Default search paths still reference old "clusterpulse" name
Problem: Lines 47-48 search for clusterpulse.yaml and ~/.clusterpulse/config.yaml. These are beta2 artifacts and should use the CloudHealth name.
Fix:
Replace lines 46-48:
DEFAULT_CONFIGS = [
    Path("config/config.yaml"),
    Path("clusterpulse.yaml"),
    Path.home() / ".clusterpulse" / "config.yaml",
]

With:
DEFAULT_CONFIGS = [
    Path("config/config.yaml"),
    Path("cloudhealth.yaml"),
    Path.home() / ".cloud_health" / "config.yaml",
]

